---
description: Testing policy and minimum expectations
alwaysApply: true
---

- Unit test utility logic in `src/lib`.
- Integration test route behavior where relevant.
- Add e2e tests for user-critical flows.
- Do not merge failing tests.
- Report coverage for changed files when available, or mark `n/a` with reason.
- Performance validation should be production-mode first (`npm run build` + `npm run start`); use dev mode only for smoke checks.

## Example

```text
Good:
- src/lib/profile.ts changed -> add tests/unit/lib/profile.test.ts
- src/app/api/profile/route.ts changed -> add tests/integration/profile-route.test.ts
- critical user flow changed -> add/update tests/e2e/profile-edit.spec.ts
- report coverage command and changed-file coverage in handoff

Bad:
- only manual testing for API changes
- skipping failing tests "for now"
- perf decision based only on next dev measurements
```
